Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.16,0:00:09.52,Default,,0,0,0,,This noise didn't certainly come from a food bell, instead now starts Marko Kahjo's storytime. 
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.02,0:00:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry for anyone hungry, who mistook it as a food bell.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.62,0:00:21.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Wise Dog.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.12,0:00:25.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Once upon a time there was a dog who according to their owners was very wise. 
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.90,0:00:33.74,Default,,0,0,0,,If you commanded to sit the dog would sit, to make it's owners happy, and to receive a treat.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.24,0:00:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you asked for a paw, the dog knew to give it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.68,0:00:41.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Again the hound would get a piece of sausage.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.58,0:00:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It would even go lie on the ground on command.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.18,0:00:50.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Well isn't that a smart dog, everyone wondered and was SO proud.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.74,0:01:01.78,Default,,0,0,0,,But, give the dog a paper full of algebraic hyperbole functions and tell it to simplify. I'm willing to bet that the dog can't do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.16,0:01:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,No. No matter how much sausage was on display.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.60,0:01:12.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, isn't that a supposedly smart dog, can't even do hyperbole functions.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.66,0:01:17.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't do them either, but I'm not a dog.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.34,0:01:25.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Security Eating
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.64,0:01:31.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Hunger is forever. Sometimes you don't feel it but you always carry it with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.30,0:01:38.78,Default,,0,0,0,,As it one in a while pops up, out of nowhere, even though you were sure the last time it went away it would stay away.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.86,0:01:45.50,Default,,0,0,0,,But no, you can't get rid of hunger forever. It waits for the opportune time to attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.80,0:01:48.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And when you get hungry, you need to eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.06,0:01:54.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes, even though you're not hungry, you anticipate the future hunger.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.88,0:02:00.60,Default,,0,0,0,,When you know that the hunger is coming, you move it even further into the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.76,0:02:03.26,Default,,0,0,0,,This is called Security Eating.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.58,0:02:09.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It is good to eat, in case you're going on a long trip, into storage.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.48,0:02:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Your body can then consume for it's own needs, that meat pie with two wieners.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.68,0:02:26.68,Default,,0,0,0,,A full stomach is much better than an empty one or a flatulent one in case you're lactose intolerant and accidently consume dairy products.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.12,0:02:30.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Security Eating can turn against itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.36,0:02:41.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Badly timed security eating, right before well timed lunch break, can make you unable to eat during the time alloted for food.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.74,0:02:51.26,Default,,0,0,0,,This in turn causes the stored energy to be consumed considerably sooner than the next time you can eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.72,0:03:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So, be careful with the timing. Weren't you already taught as a child not to eat candy before lunch so you don't lose your appetite?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.48,0:03:03.54,Default,,0,0,0,,But did you learn? No!
